{"pdf_page": 400, "w": 1434, "h": 2330, "dpi": 300, "blocks": [{"order": 0, "label": "SectionHeader", "conf": 0.961, "html": "<p>PLATE No. 14.</p>", "bbox": [560.6940000000001, 258.63, 871.872, 312.22]}, {"order": 1, "label": "SectionHeader", "conf": 0.961, "html": "<p><b>TRIMURTI.</b></p>", "bbox": [137.66400000000002, 365.81, 332.68800000000005, 414.73999999999995]}, {"order": 2, "label": "Text", "conf": 0.961, "html": "<p>The origin of the myth of the three-headed god Trimurti (page 228) <i>alias</i> Datt or Dattātreya, is traced to the Orion in this plate. <i>See</i> also Datta Jayanti, page 32.</p>", "bbox": [219.402, 466.0, 1312.1100000000001, 629.1]}]}